  "text": "A few other factors have been analyzed for and found their association with T. foetus-positive status occasionally. One is sex. Among seven studies only one demonstrated being a male kitten is a great risk factor (P < 0.01) [CITATION_1] . Another one is housing with more than one other cat. One of four surveys showed sharing house with more than five cats had an OR 4.6 (P < 0.01) [CITATION_2] . The third one is food, one of three investigations resulted in an OR 5.4 for feeding raw food diet (P < 0.01) [CITATION_3] . What causes this disparity is beyond the scope of this manuscript. Plausible reasons include small sample sizes and confounding factors.",
